Kano State governor, Dr Abdullahi Umar Ganduje has said that the All Progressives Congress (APC) presidential candidate is not an experimental president given his dexterity and strong rooting in politics and administration in the Nigeria project. This was just as the governor also thanked President Muhammadu Buhari for creating the enabling environment for the conduct of the primary, the APC and its governors, as well as other aspirants who have expressed readiness to work with Asiwaju for the victory of the party. He said given his outstanding performance as Lagos State governor, where he formed a team made up of people from different parts of the country that transformed the state into the strongest economy in the sub-region, Asiwaju’s presidency can best manage our diversity. He made the assertion at the Governor’s Lodge, Aminu Kano House, Abuja, when he received an award presented to him by the National Coalition of Tinubu Support Groups Worldwide, the national directorate, comprising Nigeria, USA, UK, Canada, Ireland, Germany, South Africa, Saudi Arabia, Brazil, Oman, UAE chapters, for his leading role in Tinubu’s victory at the party’s primary election. According to a statement signed by the state Commissioner for Information, Comrade Muhammad Garba, a copy made available on Saturday to pressmen in Kano, quoted Ganduje as saying Asiwaju’s emergence at the primary election gives hope and encouragement that the party is set to win the 2023 election. ALSO READ FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE  He expressed appreciation for the recognition by the coalition and promised to work harder for the success of Asiwaju’s presidential candidature. Earlier, the convener and global director-general of the coalition, Dr Doyin Johnson, had said that the award was presented to Governor Ganduje as way of saying thank you for the strategic role he played in the actualisation of the Asiwaju presidency. He charged the governor to continue to use his intellectual capacity and strong mobilization prowess to ensure the success of the APC presidential candidate at the polls. Also speaking, the Imo State governor, who was part of the delegation, tasked the governor whom he described as a man of honour, to further map out strategies for winning the secondary election come 2023.  